&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In an examination of 180 marks of a subject, 75% marks are allocated for theory and the rest for project work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Veena scored 60% in theory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculations:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total marks needed = 62% of 180&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; (62/100) &amp;times; 180 = 111.6&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total theory marks = 75% of 180 = 135&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total practice marks = 25% of 180 = 45&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Marks he got in theory = 60% of 135 = 81&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Required extra marks to get 62% = 111.6 - 81 = 30.6&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now, 30.6 as percentage of 45 marks&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; (30.6/45)100 = 68%&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The correct choice is option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ram and Shyam together can complete the work in 12 days.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Shyam alone can complete the work in 15 days.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Shyam alone worked for 5 days.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula Used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Work done by both together in 1 day = 1/12&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Work done by Shyam alone in 1 day = 1/15&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Work done by Ram alone in 1 day = 1/12 - 1/15&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Remaining work after Shyam worked for 5 days = Total work - Work done by Shyam in 5 days&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time taken by Ram to complete the remaining work = Remaining work / Work done by Ram in 1 day&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Work done by both together in 1 day = 1/12&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Work done by Shyam alone in 1 day = 1/15&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Work done by Ram alone in 1 day = 1/12 - 1/15&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Work done by Ram alone in 1 day = (15 - 12) / (12 &amp;times; 15)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Work done by Ram alone in 1 day = 3 / 180&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Work done by Ram alone in 1 day = 1/60&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Work done by Shyam in 5 days = 5 &amp;times; (1/15)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Work done by Shyam in 5 days = 5/15&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Work done by Shyam in 5 days = 1/3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Remaining work = 1 - 1/3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Remaining work = 2/3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time taken by Ram to complete the remaining work = (2/3) / (1/60)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Time taken by Ram to complete the remaining work = (2/3) &amp;times; 60&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Time taken by Ram to complete the remaining work = 40 days&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;A container has 20% milk and 80% water in it. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;It is mixed with another sample (in equal quantity) having 80% milk and 20% water&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

