&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let, x units of Alloy A and y units of Alloy B be&amp;nbsp;mixed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to the question,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(7x/15 + 4y/5)/(8x/15 + y/5) = 2/1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; [(7x + 12y)/15]/[8x + 3y/15] = 2/1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 7x + 12y = 16x + 6y&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 6y = 9x&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x/y = 6/9 = 2/3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; Required ratio is 2 : 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/shortcut-trick-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
