&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Average speed = Total distance/Total time&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the first distance of 100 km at a speed of 200 km/hr:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time taken = 100 km / 200 km/hr = 1/2 hr&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the second distance of 100 km at a speed of 300 km/hr:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time taken = 100 km/300 km/hr = 1/3 hr&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the third distance of 100 km at a speed of 600 km/hr:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time taken = 100 km / 600 km/hr = 1/6 hr&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total distance = 100 km + 100 km + 100 km = 300 km&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total time = 1/2&amp;nbsp;hr + 1/3 hr + 1/6 hr = 1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Average speed = 300 km/1&amp;nbsp;hr&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;300 km/hr&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the average speed of the truck for the entire journey is 300 km/hr.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

