&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Total Work = 40 &amp;times; 15 = 600&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; New Total Work = 40&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 5 + (40 + 10)&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; x (where x is the remaining time)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Setting these equal, 600 = 200 + 50x&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Solving for x, we get x = 8 days&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the total work will be completed in 8 (remaining) + 5 (initial) = 13&amp;nbsp;days.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

